org.apache.flex.compiler.fxg.swf

Class FXG2SWFTranscoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.fxg.swf.FXG2SWFTranscoder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFXGTranscoder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FlexFXG2SWFTranscoder

    public class FXG2SWFTranscoder
extends Object
implements IFXGTranscoder
    Transcodes an FXG DOM into a tree of SWF DefineSpriteTags which use SWF graphics primitives to draw the document. Note that in this implementation, since FTE based text has no equivalent in SWF tags, text nodes are ignored.

        public FXGSymbolClass transcode(IFXGNode fxgNode,
                       String packageName,
                       String className,
                       Map<ITag,ITag> extraTags,
                       Collection<ICompilerProblem> problems)
        Description copied from interface: IFXGTranscoder
        Traverses an FXG DOM to generate a SWF graphics primitives, with the root DefineSpriteTag associated with a generated ActionScript symbol class if any.
        Specified by:
        transcode in interface IFXGTranscoder
        Parameters:
        fxgNode - the root node of an FXG DOM.
        packageName - the package name of the generated symbol class.
        className - the class name of the generated symbol class.
        extraTags - any extra tags that are associated with tags in this FXG. The unit calling transcoder should add these to the frame after their keys are added.
        problems - problem collection used to collect problems occurred within this method
        Returns:
        an FXGSymbolClass context that includes generated sources and associated DefineSpriteTags.
